diligent /ˈdɪlɪdʒənt/

1. ADJ Someone who is diligent works hard in a careful and thorough way. 勤奋的 

例： Meyers is a diligent and prolific worker. 迈耶斯是个勤奋而且出活多的工人。 

2. diligence N-UNCOUNT 勤奋 

例： The police are pursuing their inquiries with great diligence. 警察正以不懈的努力进行着调查。

